The course gives an overview of methodology of language immersion.  The students have to do practical tasks, take notes of the lessons and create teaching materials.  The course also presents the world&acute;s experience of the language immersion methods as well as the Estonian experience.  The negative and positive sides of the methods are also looked at.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) give an overview of the notion of language immersion, its spreading and development in Estonia;
2) to introduce language immersion methodology and it difference from common methods of language teaching;
3) to teach how to compose a curriculum proceeding from the language immersion methodology. 4) to deal with techniques of developing reading, speaking and speech development skills in language immersion.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows subject-related notions and can define them;
2) names at least three possibilities for teacher cooperation;
3) can analyse a language immersion lesson and make suggestions on how to improve it;
4) composes teaching aids for using in a language immersion lesson.
